In their letter, they state that the UDF "is a full-fledged political movement since 1978" and recall that Mr. Morin and his friends "chosen" to leave in 2007, "to create a competitive movement, like others in 2002 to establish the UMP.
According to them, the Nouveau Centre movement has no right to use the abbreviation UDF (Union pour la démocratie francaise).
They also recall that the last UDF congress voted in 2007 to join MoDem for three years and to form a committee charged with defending the "moral and material interests" of the association founded by Valéry Giscard d'Estaing.
As for Hervé de Charette, the committee continues, "when he registered the trademark", he was "not a member of the UDF for three years" but of the UMP.
In a scandalous and fraudulent way, he used a non-existent registration acronym to do so on his own account.
This indiscretion is beginning to turn into a crime, they declare, and then ironically comment on the NC's strategy: "It seems to us that in both politics and everyday life it is more valuable to make a name for yourself than to step out of anonymity by fraudulently accepting a name to which we have no right".
