In these days of storms and accidents earn not only car repair shops.
Each day thousands of cars that have suffered an insurance claim are towed to a garage, where an expert must estimate the damage and repair costs.
No insurance event is the same, and calculating the cost of parts and labor time can be long and complex work.
Calculate manually the cost of repair from 20,000 to 30,000 euros including parts and labor can take two or three hours.
However, with the support of new computer tools it would be a matter of minutes
Therefore, almost 100% of experts use this kind of system.
Service providers and insurance and maintenance forecasting solutions are dedicated to collecting the information provided to them by manufacturers to then develop and offer their customers a useful tool.
In Spain, Audatex, from the American Solera Group is a leading company; 80% of the reviews are made with its products.
Other companies competing in the field of valuation tools and sector information are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Working with the data provided by manufacturers is not at all easy.
According to Eduard Velázquez, Sales Director of Audatex, 63 manufacturers and importers work in Spain, and each provides them with information in a different format.
In addition, the amount of data to be processed is still growing, as more versions, variants and engine solutions have been introduced in the last five years than in the previous fifteen years.
As soon as a new vehicle enters the market, these companies start to work.
This is a very feverish job, because it is necessary to catalog each of the thousands of parts of the vehicle and determine its price.
In addition, each model is carried out "intelligent" graphic processing, where it is possible to "punch" individual parts of tourist cars.
As for the model with massive sales, the work can be done in a week, if the process is very fast.
As for the minority car, it can take three or four months. At present, Audatex has complete information on 99.2% of cars sold in Spain.
The most exclusive models they have information about include Porsche, but not Ferrari or Lamborghini, for example.
In terms of the rolling park in circulation they exceed 99%.
To carry out the work of documenting and developing the databases, Audatex has eight centers spread over the world (Spain, France, Germany, USA, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan) and each of them specializes in specific brands.
The national seat is in Alcobendas (Madrid).
There, more than a hundred technicians (normally mechanics experts) work simultaneously with three computer screens.
Audatex invests EUR 90 million annually in the development of these databases.
Every month, 2.5 million data are included and customers receive updates every two days.
Processing this vast stream of information allows businesses to use and provide a variety of products.
